  "market_context": "London session (02:00–05:00 EST) swept a prior high, followed by a clear change in state of delivery (CISD) on the 30-minute chart. New York session then manipulated higher into an opposing order block before continuing lower.",
  "key_observation": "London swept a high and formed a CISD via close below a series of up-close candles; NY then manipulated up into that OB, creating a high-probability short entry with 2R target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified London session (02:00–05:00 EST) sweeping a prior high on the 15-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Analyst moved to the 30-minute chart to confirm a clean series of up-close candles into the high, then observed a close below them—confirming Change in State of Delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 3: Analyst anticipated New York would manipulate higher into the opposing candles (now forming a bearish order block) to set up a continuation lower.",
    "Step 4: At NY open (08:30), price moved higher into the OB; analyst entered short on close below the OB, placing stop above the manipulation high and targeting 2R.",
    "Step 5: Trade hit 2R as price continued lower after retesting the propulsion block around 10:00."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved 2R profit; price continued lower after NY manipulation into the order block.",
  "lessons": "A London reversal confirmed by CISD creates high-probability NY continuation setups. Always wait for NY manipulation into the opposing OB before entering—do not trade the London reversal alone. Alignment across 30-min (CISD) and 5/15-min (OB retest) is critical.",
